## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Tech: React (Next.js preferred), TypeScript, React Query for data fetching or equivalent, Zustand or Context for state if needed.
- Pages:
  - /sessions/[sessionId]: Session Viewer Page
  - /dashboard: Dashboard (existing)
  - /public-chat/[agentId]: Public Chat Page
- UI Components:
  - Card, Button, Pill, Input, Select, Table, Tag/Chips, Badge, Tooltip, Icon set (matching design system)
  - Transcript timeline with real-time streaming capability (simulate via server-sent events / WebSocket if available)
  - Field extraction table with per-field statuses
  - Export modal or in-page export controls
  - Replay controls: Play/Pause, Step, Jump to timestamp
- Data Handling:
  - Safely handle session data with null-safe accessors
  - Use data ?? [] for lists coming from API
  - Guard all array methods
- Accessibility:
  - ARIA labels for dynamic elements; keyboard navigation; screen-reader friendly

### Backend
- Tech: Node.js (Fastify/Nest), TypeScript preferred; database: PostgreSQL (via Supabase or direct), or alternative as per project.
- Data Models:
  - Sessions: id, sessionId, agentId, transcript: TranscriptMessage[], fields: FieldValueMap, metadata, timestamps, status, hooks, etc.
  - TranscriptMessage: id, sessionId, timestamp, role (user/assistant/system), content, model, prompt, tokens
  - Fields: fieldId, sessionId, label, value, source, timestamp, validationStatus, notes
  - WebhookDelivery: id, sessionId, url, attempt, status, response, signedPayload, dlqFlag
  - Annotations: id, sessionId, userId, note, tag, timestamp
  - KnowledgeLookups: sessionId, lookupKey, result
- APIs:
  - GET /api/sessions/{sessionId}
  - POST /api/sessions/{sessionId}/export (format: csv|json)
  - POST /api/sessions/{sessionId}/webhook (resend)
  - POST /api/sessions/{sessionId}/annotate
  - POST /api/sessions/{sessionId}/tag
  - POST /api/sessions/{sessionId}/mark-reviewed
  - POST /api/sessions/{sessionId}/replay
- Validation:
  - Server-side validation rules per field; deterministic outcomes
  - Ensure no crash if fields are missing; default to []
- Security:
  - Authentication for admin/dashboard endpoints; webhook endpoints validate signatures
  - External webhooks signing (HMAC) if configured
  - Rate limiting on webhook retries
- Performance:
  - Efficient pagination for transcripts; streaming where feasible
  - Debounced export for large datasets

### Integration
- Connect Frontend to Backend via REST/GraphQL API with typed responses.
- Webhooks:
  - Dispatcher ensures signed payloads when required.
  - Retries with exponential backoff and a DLQ table.
  - Provide webhook status in SessionViewer UI.
- LLM Orchestration:
  - Implement a state machine that sequences knowledge lookups, validations, and message streaming.
  - Ensure session state is persisted after each interaction.
- Data Persistence:
  - Persist every transcript line, field extraction, and metadata for auditability.
  - Exports must reconstruct the session with chronological order.

---

## User Experience Flow
1. Admin navigates to a specific Session Viewer page: /sessions/{sessionId}
2. Page loads with Transcript Panel (chronological messages), Extracted Fields Panel, Session Metadata, and Action Bar.
3. Admin views per-field validation status; can filter/sort fields by status or timestamp.
4. Admin uses Export (CSV/JSON) to download the session; progress indicator appears during export; download completes.
5. Admin taps Resend to Webhook to re-deliver all session data to configured endpoints; UI shows delivery attempts, status, and any errors.
6. Admin adds Tags/Annotations to the session; these are persisted and searchable.
7. Replay Mode: Admin toggles replay to step through messages; visual indicators show where validations occurred or knowledge lookups happened.
8. Optional: Admin marks session as Reviewed; metadata updated accordingly.

---

## Technical Specifications

Data Models (illustrative; adapt to existing schema):
- Session
  - id: string
  - agentId: string
  - startedAt: string (ISO)
  - finishedAt: string | null
  - transcript: TranscriptMessage[]
  - fields: FieldValue[]
  - metadata: SessionMetadata
  - status: "in_progress" | "completed"
- TranscriptMessage
  - id: string
  - sessionId: string
  - timestamp: string
  - role: "user" | "assistant" | "system"
  - content: string
  - model: string
  - prompt: string | null
  - tokens: number
- FieldValue
  - fieldId: string
  - sessionId: string
  - label: string
  - value: any
  - source: "user" | "extracted" | "validated"
  - timestamp: string
  - validationStatus: "valid" | "invalid" | "pending" | "error"
  - notes: string | null
- WebhookDelivery
  - id: string
  - sessionId: string
  - url: string
  - payload: string
  - attempt: number
  - status: "pending" | "success" | "failed" | "dlq"
  - responseCode: number | null
  - signedPayload: string | null
  - dlqFlag: boolean

API Endpoints (examples; align with existing project routing):
- GET /api/sessions/:sessionId
  - Returns: { sessionId, transcript, fields, metadata, status, hooks, etc. }
- POST /api/sessions/:sessionId/export
  - Body: { format: "csv" | "json" }
  - Response: file download or streaming link
- POST /api/sessions/:sessionId/webhook/resend
  - Body: { webhookId?: string, all?: boolean }
  - Response: { success: boolean, deliveries: [...] }
- POST /api/sessions/:sessionId/annotate
  - Body: { note: string, tag?: string }
- POST /api/sessions/:sessionId/tag
  - Body: { tags: string[] }
- POST /api/sessions/:sessionId/mark-reviewed
  - Body: { reviewed: boolean }

Security:
- Admin authentication for session and dashboard endpoints.
- Webhook outbound signatures (if configured) using HMAC with shared secret.
- Optional respondent verification on public chat (enabled via agent config).
- CSRF protection for state-changing endpoints; proper authentication for admin routes.

Validation:
- Server rules for field values prior to acceptance; deterministic outcomes.
- All inputs validated using strict schemas; return explicit error messages.

Validation/Testing:
- Unit tests for:
  - Safe access patterns (null-safe array handling)
  - Field validation outcomes and statuses
  - Webhook dispatch retry logic and DLQ behavior
  - Export generation for CSV/JSON
  - Replay mode sequencing and validation gates
- Integration tests for end-to-end session creation, streaming, and export
- E2E tests simulating a public chat session flow with field collection

